evaluation.evaluation_prompt_template:
You are evaluating an RFP/grant opportunity for {name}, the company behind {platform}.

Product: {product}
Mission: {mission}
Core problem being solved: {core_problem}
Primary users: {primary_users}
Key functionality: {key_functionality}
Geographic focus: {geographic_focus}
Company values: {values}
Priority themes (core to {name}'s identity — weigh these heavily when judging mission fit, even if the RFP doesn't use this exact terminology): {priority_themes}

Additional company background:
{mission_detail}

Keyword match score (0-1, higher = more overlap): {keyword_score}
Keyword matches by category:
{keyword_matches_summary}

Opportunity:
Title: {title}
Agency/Funder: {agency_or_funder}
Deadline: {deadline}
Estimated Value: {estimated_value}
Description: {description}

Evaluate how well this opportunity fits {name} and {platform}. Consider: relevance to our data-sharing and SDOH mission, geographic fit, realistic win likelihood, and any red flags such as sole-source requirements or mismatched scope.

Separately from relevance_score, give a mission_alignment_score (1-10) rating how genuinely this opportunity aligns with {name}'s mission of CBO collaboration, social care infrastructure, and health equity — judge real mission fit, not just keyword overlap. Also write a short (1-3 sentence) mission_fit_explanation in plain language, suitable for a report section titled "Why this fits {name}", explaining how this opportunity connects (or doesn't) to the company's mission.

Also provide key_requirements: 3-6 short bullet points stating what this RFP/grant is specifically looking for (scope of work, deliverables, eligibility requirements). And provide win_tip: one concise, specific, actionable tip for how {name} could strengthen its odds of winning this particular opportunity.
